South African Stocks: Anglo, AngloGold, Billiton, Exxaro, Sasol

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-06-23T15:45:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/south-african-stocks-anglo-american-billiton-exxaro-sasol.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
dropped to its lowest close since March 15, losing 466.33, or
1.5 percent, to 30,326.54 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  , the diversified mining company
that makes up 9.8 percent of  South Africa ’s benchmark stock
index, had its biggest decline since April 12, retreating 9.40
rand, or 3 percent, to 309.49 rand. Commodity prices fell the
most in seven weeks after U.S. jobless claims rose more than
economists forecast and the U.S. federal Reserve lowered its
growth estimates for the  U.S. economy .  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL)  , the world’s biggest mining
company, slipped 6.14 rand, or 2.4 percent, to 246.46 rand.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  , Africa’s largest gold
producer, headed for its lowest close in more than 14 months,
dropping 9.30 rand, or 3.2 percent, to 282.13 rand. The spot
price of gold fell 2.2 percent to $1,519.93 an ounce, its
biggest drop since Jan 4.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  , the second-biggest producer,
halted three days of gains, weakening 2.9 rand, or 3 percent, to
95.68 rand. Harmony Gold Mining Co. Ltd. (HAR SJ), Africa’s
third-largest gold producer, snapped three days of gains,
falling 4.96 rand, or 5.6 percent, to 83.29 rand.  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  , the biggest seller of coal
to South African power utility Eskom Holdings SOC Ltd., declined
1.6 rand, or 1 percent, to 164.50 rand, snapping two days of
advances. The coal miner won’t increase its offer for
 Australia ’s Territory Resources Ltd., it said in a statement.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL)  , fell for a second day, retreating 9.81
rand, or 2.8 percent, to 339 rand. Oil tumbled to the lowest
price in four months after the  International Energy Agency  said
its members would release crude from strategic reserves.  To contact the reporter on this story:
